      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The main difference is that modern civilizations are generally more complex and technologically advanced than those traditionally labeled \"primitive.\" These modern societies are characterized by specialization of labor, large-scale urbanization, and complex bureaucratic institutions. Primitive societies, in contrast, are often characterized by smaller, kinship-based groups with less division of labor and simpler social structures.",
