      "content": "i get that, history and stuff is huge. but if you look at the actual outcomes, like how much influence different parts of the world have right now, it's pretty clear that some groups ended up with much more \"advanced\" systems. does that mean some cultures are just inherently better suited for the complexity of a modern state, or do you think most groups are capable of it if they just had the right chance?",
